# Week 2 Detailed Report

## Phase
Phase 1 - Foundation

## Week
Week 2 of 6

## Theme
Authentication Backend Completion

## Goal
Deliver a complete backend authentication system that is production-oriented and ready for Week 3 frontend integration.

## Completed Implementation

### 1. Auth Domain and Routing
- Added dedicated auth route module with API endpoints under /api/v1/auth.
- Added auth route registration in the API router.
- Added auth-specific rate limiter for abuse prevention.

Implemented endpoints:
- POST /api/v1/auth/register
- POST /api/v1/auth/verify-email
- POST /api/v1/auth/login
- POST /api/v1/auth/refresh
- POST /api/v1/auth/logout
- POST /api/v1/auth/forgot-password
- POST /api/v1/auth/reset-password
- GET /api/v1/auth/me

### 2. User and Profile Data Models
- Upgraded User model with Week 2 auth fields:
  - emailVerified
  - status lifecycle (unverified, active, suspended, deleted)
  - role and plan
  - oauthProviders
  - refreshTokenFamilies
  - failedLoginAttempts and lockUntil
  - lastLoginAt and expoPushToken
- Expanded HealthProfile model with baseline targets and emergency contacts.

### 3. Security and Validation
- Added request validation schemas (Zod) for register, verify-email, login, forgot-password, reset-password.
- Added JWT access/refresh helpers and verification utilities.
- Added cookie parsing middleware for refresh-token cookie handling.
- Added structured API response helpers for success/error consistency.
- Improved error middleware for validation and custom HTTP handling.

### 4. Register and Email Verification Flow
- Register validates payload and prevents duplicate email.
- Password hashing uses bcrypt (12 rounds).
- User created in unverified state.
- Health profile stub created on registration.
- OTP generated and hashed, stored in Redis with 10-minute TTL.
- Verify-email compares OTP hash, activates account, issues token pair, and sets HTTP-only refresh cookie.

### 5. Login, Refresh Rotation, and Logout
- Login validates credentials and account status.
- Access token returned in JSON response.
- Refresh token stored as secure HTTP-only cookie.
- Refresh flow validates family record in Redis and rotates token safely.
- Reuse/invalid conditions return unauthorized and clear session path.
- Logout clears refresh cookie and removes refresh family from Redis and user state.

### 6. Forgot and Reset Password
- Forgot-password always returns generic success message for security.
- Reset token generated securely and persisted in Redis with 1-hour TTL.
- Reset-password validates token, re-hashes password, clears lock/failure state, and invalidates refresh token families.

### 7. Lockout and Rate Protection
- Added lockout behavior using Redis:
  - failed attempt counter per email
  - lock after 10 failed login attempts
  - lock duration: 30 minutes
- Added auth route rate limiting:
  - 20 requests per 15 minutes per IP

### 8. Email Service Layer
- Added email service with nodemailer support.
- Added safe fallback logging behavior when SMTP is not configured.
- Added OTP and password-reset email templates.

